      List<Type> Types.getBounds(Type.TypeVar t)
      Return list of bounds of the given type variable.
      void Types.setBounds(Type.TypeVar t, List<Type> bounds)
      Same as Types#setBounds(TypeVar, List, boolean), except that third parameter is computed directly, as follows: if all all bounds are interface types, the computed supertype is Object,otherwise the supertype is simply left null (in this case, the supertype is assumed to be the head of the bound list passed as second argument).
      void Types.setBounds(Type.TypeVar t, List<Type> bounds, boolean allInterfaces)
      Set the bounds field of the given type variable to reflect a (possibly multiple) list of bounds.
